definition: to cover/to wrap/to hold/to include/to take charge of/to contract (to or for)/package/wrapper/container/bag/to hold or embrace/bundle/packet/CL:個|个[ge4],隻|只[zhi1]

sentences.english: Both bags had names written inside them, although these were not released.
sentences.chinese: 兩個包袋內都寫有名字，雖然這些名字未予公佈。

sentences.english: This is a company specialized in producing all kinds of bags of wholly foreign-owned enterprises.
sentences.chinese: 本公司是一家專業生產各種包袋的外商獨資企業。

sentences.english: Don't man-handle the package. Most bugs love the top of a package.
sentences.chinese: 不要人工搬運包袋，蟲子多喜愛附着在袋中上游部分。

sentences.english: No matter regardless past, now, or future, bags always accompany you.
sentences.chinese: 無論是過去，現在，將來，包袋將會一直伴你左右。

sentences.english: When leaving company, open your bag or luggage positively at the entrance to let guard have inspection.
sentences.chinese: 下班離廠時，請自覺包袋讓門衛檢查。

sentences.english: The retanning and finishing technology of Jining goat skin soft bag leather was studied .
sentences.chinese: 對濟寧路山羊軟包袋革復鞣及整飾工藝進行了研究。

sentences.english: Main goods are garments. Also dealing with shoes and bags.
sentences.chinese: 主要以服裝爲主，鞋帽和包袋也有。

definition: bag or purse etc/small bump or pimple/hillock
a buckle or fastener for clothing that does not use a button and buttonhole (e.g. the buckle on metal wristwatches)
